(1).ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest kya hai?
👉 AccountRequest = ek specific application account ke liye request
📌 Matlab:-
👉 “Kisi particular application (AD / SAP / DB) me account ke saath kya karna hai”

🔹 3. Example se samajh 💡
👉 Tum bolte ho:-
john.doe ke liye:-
- AD me account create karo
- SAP me role change karo

👉 Internally:-
AD → AccountRequest
SAP → AccountRequest
✔ Har application ke liye alag AccountRequest.

🔹 4. Code example:-
ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest acc = 
    new ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest();

acc.setApplication("AD");
acc.setNativeIdentity("jdoe123");
acc.setOperation(ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Create);
plan.add(acc);
-------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 5. AccountRequest kya karta hai? ⚙️
👉 Ye batata hai:-
✔ Kaunsa application
✔ Kaunsa account
✔ Kya action (create / modify / delete)
✔ Kaunse attributes change honge
-------------------------------------------------------
🔹 6. AccountRequest ke andar kya kya hota hai? 🧠
Main fields 👇
🔸 1. application:-
👉 Kaunsa system
AD / SAP / DB

🔸 2. nativeIdentity:-
👉 External system ka username
jdoe123

🔸 3. operation:-
👉 Kya karna hai
Create / Modify / Delete / Enable / Disable

🔸 4. attributeRequests:-
👉 Field-level changes
email = new@mail.com
role = Admin
👉 Ye ek list hoti hai

🔸 5. objectRequests:-
👉 Groups / roles / entitlements ke changes

🔸 6. arguments:-
👉 Extra parameters (optional)

🔸 7. instance:-
👉 Application instance (prod/test)

🔸 8. trackingId:-
👉 Request tracking ke liye
--------------------------------------------------------
🔹 9. DB me store hota hai kya? 🧠
👉 ❌ Directly AccountRequest DB me store nahi hota
👉 Kyunki:-
✔ Ye runtime object hai

✅ Lekin indirectly store hota hai:-
🔸 1. spt_provisioning_transaction
👉 Provisioning logs

🔸 2. spt_audit_event
👉 Audit trail

🔸 3. spt_task_result
👉 Execution result
----------------------------------------------------------
🔹 2. 🔥 Core Methods:-
🔸 1. setApplication(String app):-
👉 Kaunsa application target hai
acc.setApplication("AD");
✔ Use: AD / SAP / DB set karne ke liye

🔸 2. getApplication():-
String app = acc.getApplication();
✔ Output: "AD"

🔸 3. setNativeIdentity(String id):-
👉 External system ka username
acc.setNativeIdentity("jdoe123");

🔸 4. getNativeIdentity():-
String id = acc.getNativeIdentity();
✔ Output: "jdoe123"

🔸 5. setOperation(Operation op):-
👉 Kya action lena hai
acc.setOperation(ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Create);
Possible values:
Create
Modify
Delete
Enable
Disable

🔸 6. getOperation():-
Operation op = acc.getOperation();
✔ Output: Create

🔹 3. 🔥 AttributeRequest Methods:-
🔸 7. add(AttributeRequest attr):-
👉 Attribute add karne ke liye
AttributeRequest attr = new AttributeRequest();
attr.setName("email");
attr.setValue("john@example.com");
acc.add(attr);

🔸 8. getAttributeRequests():-
List attrs = acc.getAttributeRequests();
✔ Output: List of attributes

🔸 9. setAttributeRequests(List list):-
acc.setAttributeRequests(list);

🔹 4. 🔥 ObjectRequest Methods:-
🔸 10. add(ObjectRequest obj):-
ObjectRequest obj = new ObjectRequest();
acc.add(obj);
👉 Groups / roles ke liye

🔸 11. getObjectRequests():-
List objs = acc.getObjectRequests();

🔹 5. 🔥 Arguments / Extra Data:-
🔸 12. setArguments(Map args):-
Map args = new HashMap();
args.put("key", "value");
acc.setArguments(args);

🔸 13. getArguments():-
Map args = acc.getArguments();

🔹 6. 🔥 Instance Methods:-
🔸 14. setInstance(String instance):-
acc.setInstance("Production");

🔸 15. getInstance():-
String inst = acc.getInstance();

🔹 7. 🔥 Tracking / Metadata:-

🔸 16. setTrackingId(String id):-
acc.setTrackingId("REQ123");

🔸 17. getTrackingId():-
String id = acc.getTrackingId();

🔹 8. 🔥 Utility Methods:-

🔸 18. toString():-
👉 Object ka readable format
System.out.println(acc.toString());

🔸 19. equals(Object obj):-
👉 Compare karta hai

🔸 20. hashCode():-
👉 Hash value generate karta hai.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

////////*
🔹 3. accReq.getAttributeRequest("sAMAccountName") kya karta hai?
✅ Explanation:
sailpoint.object.AttributeRequest sam =
    accReq.getAttributeRequest("sAMAccountName");
👉 Ye method:-
AccountRequest ke andar se attribute fetch karta hai
"sAMAccountName" = AD username attribute

🔹 Return kya hota hai?
👉 Return type:-
sailpoint.object.AttributeRequest
Agar attribute exist karta hai:-
object return karega

🔹 4. sam.getValue() kya return karega?
Object value = sam.getValue();
👉 Ye return karega:-
attribute ka actual value
Example:-
Agar provisioning plan me hai:-
<sAMAccountName>john.doe</sAMAccountName>
To:-
sam.getValue();  // returns "john.doe"
*////////
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------